PROCEDURE: UK Enterprise KYC & AML Onboarding
TRIGGER: New corporate client registers on the financial platform
TOOLS: companies_house_api, identity_verification, aml_screening_db

1. Greet the client representative and request the UK Company Registration Number
2. Lookup the company details using companies_house_api
3. Check if the company status is "Active"
   - YES: Proceed to step 4
   - NO: Inform the client that only active companies can be onboarded and end
4. Verify the identity of the representative using identity_verification
5. Check if the verified identity matches an active Director
   - YES: Proceed to step 6
   - NO: Escalate to compliance_officer for manual review
6. Query aml_screening_db to screen the company and directors against UK PEPs and sanctions
7. Check if there are any sanctions matches or high-risk flags
   - YES: Escalate to compliance_officer
   - NO: Proceed to step 8
8. Ask the client to upload their proof of business address (Utility bill or Bank statement)
9. Confirm successful automated KYC onboarding and notify client of account activation and end
